  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The study is a clinical evaluation of an over the counter (OTC) combination product
      containing paracetamol (500 mg), dimethindene maleate (1 mg), phenylephrine hydrochloride (10
      mg) compared to paracetamol (500 mg) alone in the treatment of nasal congestion, rhinorrhea,
      sneezing and other symptoms due to upper respiratory tract infection (URTI).
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
